</p>
<p>The impact of a heartfelt condolence message should not be underestimated.  A thoughtfully composed message can offer solace and a sense of shared grief, helping the bereaved begin the process of healing.  Remember to keep your message brief and focused on the deceased and their positive attributes.  Avoid generic phrases and focus on personal memories or shared experiences to create a more meaningful and personalized expression of sympathy.</p>
    

